A KZN pastor who has been missing for four days was found dead near a Greytown farm on Friday. Pastor Siyabonga Mashaba (36) of the Greytown Spoken Word Fellowship was found dead with a stab wound in the back of his neck. It’s alleged that Mashaba was hijacked last week. His vehicle was found abandoned in the area after it crashed into another car on the R74 last week. A local security company and the police found the car abandoned and alerted the family. Church spokesperson Celukuthula Makhathini said, “The congregation is saddened by the murder of its leader. He was a good man with a sense of humanity. He was gifted spiritually. “I last saw him last Sunday. On Monday, I received a call from the members of the church reporting that the pastor’s car had been found abandoned in the bush. “We started looking for him in hospitals, but could not find any leads.” He added: “We were shocked because the pastor is a man of God, he didn’t keep such items in his car. “I reported a case of a missing person in Greytown. Last week, I received a call from the police alerting us that there was a body found near the farm. “Upon arrival at the scene, I was shocked to see the pastor’s body dumped in the bush,” said Makhathini. Mashaba’s sister Lydia said the family is devastated at her brother’s death. She said: KZN police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala said a case of murder was opened at Greytown police station for investigation. The motive for the killing is unknown.